  "description": "An attention-grabbing hero anchored by twin scrolling marquee strips with editorial typography. Designed for fashion drops, festivals, agencies, and brands that lead with personality and movement.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Two opposing horizontal marquees frame an asymmetric content block. Oversized serif words travel across the viewport with a subtle italic counter-row beneath, separated by a colored glyph that adopts the brand accent. Headline and CTA sit in a 12-column split that reads naturally without centering everything.",
    "usage": "Best for openers where energy and rhythm are part of the brand promise. Works for product drops, event campaigns, creative agencies, music labels, and any site that benefits from kinetic typography rather than a static image-led hero.",
    "audienceFit": "Resonates with creative-led audiences, younger demographics, and brands that already lean editorial or fashion-forward. Reads as confident and current to viewers who associate movement with cultural relevance."
